Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a syntactical and semantic analyzer for French based on categorial grammars and Montague semantics, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of logical formulae for inferences and the proposal of a solution inspired by the tau and epsilon operators of Hilbert suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of determiners and quantifiers also implies a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
